\pard\plain \intbl\itap1\sa160\qj{\f1\fs20\b1 Quick Bit}{\f0\fs22  The Hebrew word }{\f0\fs22\i1 mishpat}{\f0\fs22  means \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93justice\u8221\'94 or \u8220\'93judgment.\u8221\'94 It can refer to laws (Psa 119:7) or the carrying out of legal decisions, as in \u8220\'93executing justice\u8221\'94 or \u8220\'93bringing someone into judgment\u8221\'94 (Psa 146:7; Eccl 12:14). Proverbs claims that evil men cannot understand }{\f0\fs22\i1 mishpat}{\f0\fs22 \hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 only those who seek God can (Prov 28:5). God\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s }{\f0\fs22\i1 mishpat}{\f0\fs22  includes both condemning the guilty and vindicating the righteous (1 Kgs 8:32).}
